  "prompt": "What do hands in pockets symbolize?",
  "response": "Hands in pockets can symbolize different things depending on the context and the individual's body language. Here are some possible interpretations:\n\n1. **Casualness or Relaxation**: Often, people put their hands in their pockets when they feel comfortable and relaxed. It can be a sign of a casual, laid-back attitude.\n\n2. **Insecurity or Nervousness**: Conversely, it can also indicate insecurity or nervousness. Some people put their hands in their pockets as a self-soothing gesture when they feel anxious or unsure.\n\n3. **Disinterest or Boredom**: It might also signal disinterest or boredom, especially if accompanied by other non-verbal cues like slouching or looking away.\n\n4. **Concealment**: Sometimes, hands in pockets can be an attempt to hide something, either literally (like fidgeting hands) or figuratively (like nervousness or deceit).\n\n5. **Cultural Differences**: In some cultures, putting hands in pockets can be considered rude or disrespectful, especially in formal settings or when speaking to someone of higher social status.\n\nUnderstanding the specific meaning often requires considering the broader context, including other body language signals and the situation in which it occurs.",
